    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>
                <date>October 16th 1851</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p>Trusting that this letter will reach you in time for the <date>November</date><lb/>
                Occident, I'll make you acquainted with the proceedings of a general<lb/> meeting of
                this congregation, held last night.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In short, all and every one of the old officers were
                unani,<lb/>mously re-elected. The same was the case with me. A more<lb/> quiet,
                friendly, untied and orderly meeting was never witnessed<lb/> After the adjournment
                the President <persName>M. Strau<del>s</del>s</persName>, <persName>E.
                    Lieber,<lb/>man</persName>, <persName>Abm Gerstly</persName>, <persName>L.
                    Lowensahn</persName>, <persName>S. Ullman</persName>, <persName>T.
                    Tessil</persName>, <persName>L. Silberman</persName> and others.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I feel happy indeed, not because I am re-elected, but<lb/> for the
                friendly spirit, for the harmony and union which exists<lb/> at present in this
                congregation—and I may flatter myself that<lb/> my own humble exertions have added,
                the least, something to<lb/> this happy state of congregational affairs.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">All the officers, without exception are well worthy our<lb/>
                meriting the confidence, the respect and esteem <del>of</del> they acquired.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please take notice of these few lines, without taking notice<lb/> of
                my bad english.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I shall soon seek for an opportunity to let you hear<lb/> from me
                again</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">truly and sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">BH. Gotthelf</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P.S. The Hebrew Benevolent Ladys Society No I.</p>
            <p>held their meeting the day previous and re-elected<lb/> all their
                    officers—<persName>Mrs B. Marks</persName> President. I took several times
                occasion<lb/> to report to you their harmony and their many benevolent and
                charitable<lb/> acts, but as yet you have omitted to mention anything about it.</p>
        </body>
